2), pp. 391-405; Schlesinger, M.E., Ramankutty, N., Implications for global warming of intercycle solar irradiance variations (1992) Nature, 360, pp. 330-333; Shindell, D.T., Schmidt, G.A., Mann, M.E., Rind, D., Waple, A., Solar forcing of regional climate change during the Maunder Minimum (2001) Science, 294 (5549), pp. 2149-2152; Stott, P.A., Tett, S.F.B., Jones, G.S., Allen, M.R., Ingram, W.J., Mitchell, J.F.B., Attribution of twentieth century temperature change to natural and anthropogenic causes (2001) Clim. Dyn., 17 (1), pp. 1-21; Stuiver, M., Braziunas, T.F., Sun, ocean, climate and atmospheric CO2: An evaluation of causal and spectral relationships (1993) Holocene, 3 (4), pp. 289-305; Stuiver, M., Braziunas, T.F., Grootes, P.M., Zielinski, G.A., Is there evidence for solar forcing of climate in the GISP2 oxygen isotope record? (1997) Quat. Res., 48 (3), pp. 259-266; Waple, A.M., Mann, M.E., Bradley, R.S., Long-term patterns of solar irradiance forcing in model experiments and proxy based surface temperature reconstructions (2002) Clim. Dyn., 18 (7), pp. 563-578; White, W.B., Cayan, D.R., Lean, J., Global upper ocean heat storage response to radiative forcing from changing solar irradiance and increasing greenhouse gas/aerosol concentrations (1998) J. Geophys. Res., 103 (C10), pp. 21355-21366; Wigley, T.M.L., The climate of the past 10000 years and the role of the Sun (1988) Secular Solar and Geomagnetic Variations in the Last 10,000 Years, pp. 209-224. , Stephenson, F. R. and Wolfendale, A. W. (eds.), Kluwer Academic, Dordrecht; Wigley, T.M.L., Jones, P.D., Raper, S.C.B., The observed global warming record: What does it tell us? (1997) Proc. Nat. Acad. Sci. USA, 94 (16), pp. 8314-8320; Willson, R.C., Hudson, H.S., The Sun's luminosity over a complete solar cycle (1991) Nature, 351 (6321), pp. 42-44","Damon, P.E.; Department of Geosciences, University of Arizona, Tucson, AZ, United States; email: damon@geo.arizona.edu",,,,,,,,01650009,,CLCHD,,"English","Clim